INSERT INTO `entries_en` VALUES (1,'Cluster Technology','Cluster_Technology','/a/lb/2010/0920/766.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' Cluster is a group work set...','_Cluster_is_a_group_work_set','2010-09-20','2010-11-16 09:27:20','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td> <span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><br /> Cluster is a group work set of services, to provide more stable than a single service, more efficient, more scalable platform, the outside, the cluster is an independent service entity, but in fact, in the cluster Internally, there are two or more entities in the coordination of services, with the completion of a complex task. <br /> Clusters of two or more generally formed from a server, each server is called a cluster node, the cluster nodes can communicate with each other, communicate in two ways, one is based on the RS232 line heart rate monitor, Another is to use a separate card to run the heartbeat, therefore, the cluster service with the state monitoring function between the nodes, but also must have the extension service entities, the flexibility to add and remove a service entity. <br /> In the cluster, the same services can be provided by multiple service entities. Thus, when a node fails, another node in the cluster automatically take over the failed node\'s resources to ensure service lasting, uninterrupted operation. Thus the transfer function of the cluster with automatic fault. <br /> A cluster must have a shared data storage, because the services provided outside the cluster is the same, any one cluster node to run an application, the application of the data are centrally stored in the node shared space, each node of the operating system only running application services, application files stored. <br /> In summary, to build a cluster system requires at least two servers, but also need to have the serial line, cluster software, shared storage devices (such as disk arrays) and so on. <br /> Based <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\">Linux</a></u> cluster with its very high computing power, scalability, availability and more cost-effective optimization of a variety of applications in the enterprise to stand out. Become a concern for all <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\">Linux</a></u> applications hot, master knowledge of Linux clusters, low price can be used to make high-performance applications. To enterprises and individuals to save costs. Large domestic Sina, Netease, adopted high-performance linux cluster building web applications, using the famous search engine google linux servers on a million, a large cluster, the cluster of these instances shows the status of the application in linux and important sex. <br /> <strong>2 Characteristics and function of the cluster</strong> <br /> 2.1 High availability and scalability <br /> 1. High availability for some very strong real-time applications, must ensure that the service runs 24 hours a day, and as software, hardware, network, human and other reasons, a single service operating environment difficult to meet this requirement at this time build a cluster system is a good choice to build one of the greatest advantages of the cluster with high availability cluster, the service fails, the cluster system can automatically switch the service from the failed node to another backup node to provide uninterrupted service, ensure the continued operation of the business. <br /> 2. Scalability with the increasing volume of business, the existing entity can not meet the needs of the cluster service, you can dynamically to the cluster, add one or more service nodes, to meet application needs, and enhance the overall performance of the cluster. This is the scalability of the cluster. <br /> 2.2 load balancing and error recovery <br /> 1. Load balance cluster system can be characterized most flexible and efficient load-sharing system, by its own definition of the cluster load sharing strategy, the client\'s access to all services assigned to the following node, for example, you can define Lunxun allocation strategy, the request Pingjun allocation to each service node, you can also define the minimum load allocation strategy, when a request comes in, determine which service node cluster system are relatively free to distribute this request to this node. <br /> 2. Error recovery when a node in a task not yet complete, for some reason fails, time, and then another service node should be able to accomplish this task, which is the cluster to provide error recovery, through error redirection to ensure that each mission can be effectively completed. <br /> 2.3 IP heartbeat detection and drift <br /> 1. Heart rate monitoring in order to achieve load balancing, providing high availability services and the implementation of error recovery, the cluster system provides the heartbeat monitoring, heart rate monitoring is achieved through the heartbeat, the heartbeat of the equipment can do a RS 232 serial line can also be used independently heartbeat to run a piece of card can also be a shared disk arrays, the number of heartbeat cluster nodes should be decreased by 1, note that if the heartbeat through the card to do so, each node has two network cards, of which a private network as the machine is connected directly to each other the appropriate card, to monitor each heartbeat. Also a connection to the outside public network to provide services, while heart rate card and IP card services, as not in a subnet address. Direct impact on the efficiency of the heart rate monitor the duration of failover, the cluster system is maintained through the heart technology and effective communication between nodes inside. <br /> 2. Drift IP address in the cluster system, in addition to each service node itself the real IP address, IP address there is a drift, then why is the drift IP, because the IP addresses are not fixed, for example, double the two nodes hot standby, the normal state, the drift of IP in the master node, when the primary node fails, the drift IP address automatically switches to the standby node, therefore, in order to ensure uninterrupted service in the cluster system, external provision of services IP must be to the drift IP address, although the IP node itself can also offer services, but when the node failure, the service switched to another node, but the service failed node IP is still IP address, this time, the service with the interrupt.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><strong>Category 3 Cluster <br /></strong> 3.1 High Availability Cluster <br /> 1. The concept of high availability in English stands for High Availability Cluster High Availability Cluster, referred to as HA Cluster, the maximum availability of the means available, from the name of the cluster can be seen, the function of these Clusters is to protect the user\'s application program lasting, uninterrupted service. <br /> When an application fails, or the system hardware, network failure, the application can automatically, quickly switching from one node to another node, in order to ensure application of sustained, uninterrupted service outside, which is to achieve high-availability clustering functions <br /> 2. Common HA Cluster <br /> We often say that the hot standby, dual-prepared, multi-machine equipment and so on are each other\'s areas of high availability clusters, these clusters typically have two or more nodes. A typical hot standby structure shown in Figure 1:</span></span> </p><div style=\"text-align: center\"> <span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"182\" onclick=\"window.open(\'/uploads/allimg/100920/1_100920093219_1.png\')\" src=\"http://www.ixdba.net/uploads/allimg/100920/1_100920093219_1.png\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" width=\"384\" /><br /><br /> Figure 1 Structure of Hot Standby</span></span> </div><p> <span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Hot Standby mode is the simplest application, that is often said that the active / standby mode, it uses two servers, one as the master server (action), run the application outside service, the other as a standby machine (standby ), installation and application as the main server, but did not start the service, is in the standby state. Between the host and prepare machine technology with each other through the heartbeat monitoring, monitoring of the resources can be network, operating system, and also the service, the user can according to your needs, choose the resources need to be monitored, when monitoring and controlling equipment to host a resource failure, according to a predetermined strategy, first IP switch over, then the application services are taken over, and then to provide services outside the preparation unit, the switching time is end of the process, users simply do not feel out of the program issues, but also for the switching, in order to protect the application lasting, uninterrupted service. <br /> Dual Active in hot standby, based on two independent applications to run simultaneously on two machines, Internet-based equipment, which is prepared by two servers both host machine, when any one application fails, another server in a short time can be taken over the application of machine malfunction, in order to protect the service continued, uninterrupted operation. Dual Active advantage is saving equipment resources, the two hot standby application requires at least four servers, and Dual Active only two servers to complete high-availability clustering capabilities, but also have Dual Active the shortcomings of its own: in a node failover, another node to run the two applications to the service, there may be the case load is too large. <br /> Preparation of multi-machine interaction is a hot standby of the technology upgrade, through a cluster composed of multiple machines can be set up between multiple machines over a flexible strategy, for example, a server cluster environment composed of 8, 3 runs web applications, 3 applications to run mail, therefore, the remaining one can be as prepared 3 sets of web server machines, 3 sets another mail server as a reserve unit, through such arrangements, adequate and reasonable use of the server resources, but also to ensure the system\'s high availability. <br /> Note that: high-availability cluster can not guarantee the security of application data, it is only lasting solution is to provide uninterrupted service of external, to the software, hardware, networking, human factors failures reduce the impact of the application to the lowest level. <br /> 3. High Availability Cluster high-availability cluster software is generally achieved through the high-availability software, commonly used in high availability under linux software: open source heartbea HA, Redhat provides RHCS, business software ROSE, keepalived and so on. In the following sections we will detail heartbea HA configuration and use. <br /> 3.2 Load Balancing Load balancing system, the English full name Load Balance Cluster, referred to as LB Cluster, the load balancing cluster also has two or more than two servers, divided into front end and back-end node services load scheduling of two parts, the load scheduling partially responsible for the client\'s request in accordance with the policies assigned to different back-end service node, and back-end nodes is the real part of providing application services. <br /> The difference is that with HA Cluster in the load balancing cluster, all the back-end nodes are active, they offer services, work load sharing system. <br /> Load balancing cluster can be applied to a high load across multiple nodes to jointly complete for the busy business, access to a large load applications, but it also has deficiencies: When a node fails, the front-end dispatch system does not that this node can no longer provide services, will continue to dispatch client requests to the failed node up, so that access will fail, in order to solve this problem, the load scheduling system generally introduces a node monitoring system. <br /> Node monitoring system is located on the front-end load dispatcher responsible for monitoring the following service node, when a node fails, the node monitoring system failed node will automatically be removed from the cluster, when the node is back to normal, the node monitoring system will automatically add it to the cluster, all of this, the user is completely transparent. <br /> Figure 2 shows the basic structure of the cluster load balancing: <br /></span></span> </p><div style=\"text-align: center\"> <span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"278\" onclick=\"window.open(\'/uploads/allimg/100920/1_100920093137_1.png\')\" src=\"http://www.ixdba.net/uploads/allimg/100920/1_100920093137_1.png\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" width=\"536\" /><br /> Figure 2, the basic framework of the cluster load balancing</span></span> </div><pstyle = &quot;text-align: left&quot;&gt; <span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">load balancing cluster can be achieved by software can also be done by the hardware, linux software under a typical load balancing: LVS cluster open source, Oracle\'s RAC cluster, etc., hardware load balancing F5 Networks and other devices have. About LVS cluster, in the following chapters we will explain in detail. <br /> 3.3 scientific computing high performance computing cluster (High Perfermance Computing) clusters, referred to as HPC clusters. Such clustering is committed to providing a single computer can provide a powerful computing capabilities, including numerical computation and data processing, and tend to the pursuit of overall performance. HPC and supercomputing is similar, but there are different, the calculation speed is the first goal of the pursuit of super-computing. The fastest speed, maximum storage, the volume of the largest and most expensive prices represent the characteristics of supercomputing, as people demand to improve computing speed, super calculations applied to various fields, the pursuit of a single computing speed supercomputing the pursuit of performance indicators into composite indicators. The high performance computing. <br /> A wide range of HPC applications, typical applications include: life science research, genetic testing comparison, data mining, oil and gas exploration, image rendering and so on. <br /></span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' Cluster is a group work set of services, to provide more stable than a single service, more efficient, more scalable platform, the outside, the cluster is an independent service entity, but in fact, in the cluster Internally, there are two or more entities in the coordination of services, with the...'),(2,'Cluster Technology','Cluster_Technology','/a/lb/2010/0711/301.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' On a shared storage device....','_On_a_shared_storage_device','2010-07-11','2010-11-16 09:27:30','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td> On a shared storage device. When a server provides services directly in the storage device to read and write. When the system switch, another server also reads the data on the storage device. </p><p> For pure software approach, through the mirroring software, the data can be copied to another server in real time, so that the same data on the existence of a two servers, if one server fails, you can switch to another time servers. </p><p> Pure software approach to a certain extent, reduce costs, but it also has very significant disadvantages: </p><p> 1. Reliability is relatively poor, the two real-time replication of data between servers is a relatively weak link. </p><p> 2. Once a server interruption, even after the resumption for more sophisticated data synchronization recovery. And, this time the system is not protected. </p><p> 3. There is no transaction mechanism, because of its replication is in the file and disk layer, and copy the database transaction will not affect the success of operations, it is a complete change of data is not the case, there is considerable risk in this. </p><p> Therefore, it is recommended unless a last resort, do not choose a software program. </p><p> On the other hand, there is a parallel database solution, it is not in the file or copy the disk layer, but directly on the database front-end routing in distribution operations, in parallel to complete the database update transaction mechanism, but also can provide the database parallel service. In this way the current application for SQL SERVER very successful, much better than shared memory mode + dual machine software </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' On a shared storage device. When a server provides services directly in the storage device to read and write. When the system switch, another server also reads the data on the storage device.  For pure software approach, through the mirroring software, the data can be copied to another server in...'),(3,'Cluster Technology','Cluster_Technology','/a/lb/2010/0711/300.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' The RAC environment, a OCFS...','_The_RAC_environment_a_OCFS','2010-07-11','2010-11-16 09:27:36','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td> The RAC environment, a OCFS volume inode node has been used, but the database still running. <br /> Files can be properly created, the <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/\">system</a></u> of several conditions as follows: </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">OS: LINUXAS3 U3 <br /> ORACLE: ORACLE9204 RAC</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">The following is the specific show, / U04 produce only two-node storage of archive log</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">[Root @ db1 /] # cat / etc / issue <br /> Red Hat Enterprise Linux AS release 3 (Taroon Update 3)</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">[Root @ db1 /] # rpm-qa | grep ocfs <br /> ocfs-support-1.0.10-1 <br /> ocfs-tools-1.0.10-1 <br /> ocfs-2.4.21-EL-smp-1.0.13-1</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">[Root @ db1 /] # df-h <br /> Filesystem Size Used Avail Use% Mounted on <br /> / Dev/emcpowerd1 50G 44M 50G 1% / u04</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">[Root @ db1 /] # df-i <br /> Filesystem Inodes IUsed IFree IUse% Mounted on <br /> / Dev/emcpowerd1 409580 409231 349 100% / u04</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><br /> Finally, the author found an explanation from Metalink, that OCFS file system and is usually different, inodes are not here to play the role of the file system normally. <br /> This is the characteristics of OCFS, it is normal.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">References that explain the record as follows:</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">@ OCFS does not have the concept of inodes, however, for the vfs layer in the <br /> @ Kernel we need to fill out structures. The number returned by df-i is <br /> @ Based on diskspace free. It\'s the number of clusterblocsk in the filesystem <br /> @ We dont \'preallocate inodes like most filesystems do. Nor do we HAVE to do <br /> @ That. Not a bug, expected behaviour, not required to do what any other <br /> @ Filesystem does. <br /></span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' The RAC environment, a OCFS volume inode node has been used, but the database still running.  Files can be properly created, the system of several conditions as follows: OS: LINUXAS3 U3  ORACLE: ORACLE9204 RACThe following is the specific show, / U04 produce only two-node storage of archive...'),(4,'Cluster Technology','Cluster_Technology','/a/lb/2010/0711/299.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' Lifekeeper software from NCR...','_Lifekeeper_software_from_NCR','2010-07-11','2010-11-16 09:27:43','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td> Lifekeeper software from NCR Corporation and the leading U.S. AT &amp; T Bell Labs. For enterprises, banks and government information services, business services, government services, providing high availability solutions. </p><p> LifeKeeper high availability fault-tolerant cluster software is running on NT, Windows 2000, Linux and NCR Unix platforms. Way to support both software-mirrored disk array cabinets and shared approach and real-time replication to support remote disaster backup and recovery system. So that the user\'s servers, operating systems, database systems and critical data and applications to keep 7 days ÃƒÂ— 24 hours of continuous uninterrupted, providing 99.99% availability. Software includes a number of core parts and for different applications ARK. </p><p> The key features of LifeKeeper </p><p><br /> 1. Without any additional investment in hardware, pure software approach to achieve Fault-tolerant, and to the preparation machine without hardware configuration requirements. <br /><br /> 2. Support for Notes, Exchange, SQL Server, Sybase, Informix, Oracle, SAP and other application-level heat recovery system. <br /><br /> 3. Is the world\'s first set of NT-based operating system supports fault-tolerant software and LINUX platforms. Remote disaster recovery. <br /><br /> 4. Support the expansion of shared disk array cabinets and mirrors in two ways, give users the flexibility to choose, but also to adapt to a variety of models, network architecture, software platforms and applications. <br /><br /> 5. LifeKeeper in shared disk array mirrored or extended any way, can achieve two servers running different applications and their mutual hot backup, the dual Active operation mode. <br /><br /> 6. Shared disk array cabinet mode, can support up to 16 nodes, much larger than other similar systems are supported by two nodes. <br /><br /> 7. Maximize the protection of the client application continuity. The user\'s hardware resources (such as network cards), software resources (such as the NT operating system, database management systems, database applications, e-mail systems, etc.) can in under LifeKeeper protection, conservation of resources when these are a technical failure, LifeKeeper implementation of system resources can be switched at any time. So, LifeKeeper truly a user\'s hardware or software failure of the system resources and application-layer switch on the hot line. <br /><br /> 8. LifeKeeper minimal system resources, without increasing network load, and do not disturb any specific application of any operation. <br /><br /> 9. LifeKeeper truly unattended, automatic application of resources to achieve change, and the graphics interface operation, simple and convenient. <br /><br /> 10. Since put into use, has undergone a large number of transactions the actual peak of the test, its implementation is very efficient and reliable operation, the global market share first. <br /></p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' Lifekeeper software from NCR Corporation and the leading U.S. AT & T Bell Labs. For enterprises, banks and government information services, business services, government services, providing high availability solutions.  LifeKeeper high availability fault-tolerant cluster software is running on NT,...'),(5,'Cluster Technology','Cluster_Technology','/a/lb/2010/0711/298.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' p address  2,...','_p_address__2','2010-07-11','2010-11-16 09:27:54','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td> p address <br /> 2, real-service-address: refers to the real server ip address <br /> 3, scheduler: Scheduling </p><p><br /> ipvsadm usage and format are as follows: <br /> QUOTE: <br /> ipvsadm-A | E-t | u | f virutal-service-address: port [-s scheduler] [-p <br /> [Timeout]] [-M netmask] <br /> ipvsadm-D-t | u | f virtual-service-address <br /> ipvsadm-C <br /> ipvsadm-R <br /> ipvsadm-S [-n] <br /> ipvsadm-a | e-t | u | f service-address: port-r real-server-address: port <br /> [-G | i | m] [-w weight] <br /> ipvsadm-d-t | u | f service-address-r server-address <br /> ipvsadm-L | l [options] <br /> ipvsadm-Z [-t | u | f service-address] <br /> ipvsadm - set tcp tcpfin udp <br /> ipvsadm - start-daemon state [- mcast-interface interface] <br /> ipvsadm - stop-daemon <br /> ipvsadm-h </p><p> Command options explained: </p><p> There are two command-option format, long and short, has the same meaning. In actual use, the two can be. <br /> -A - add-service virtual server table in the kernel to add a new virtual server records. Is adding a new virtual server. <br /> -E - edit-service edit the kernel virtual server table in a virtual server record. <br /> -D - delete-service Delete the kernel virtual server table in a virtual server record. <br /> -C - clear clear kernel virtual server table all records. <br /> -R - restore restore virtual server rules <br /> -S - save to save the virtual server rules for the-R option readable output format <br /> -A - add-server virtual server table in the kernel to add a record a new record of the real server. That is, in a virtual server, add a new real server <br /> -E - edit-server editing a virtual server records in the record on a particular real server <br /> -D - delete-server virtual server to delete a record in the record on a particular real server <br /> -L |-l - list Display the kernel virtual server table <br /> -Z - zero virtual service table counter is cleared (clear the current number of connections, etc.) <br /> - Set tcp tcpfin udp set the connection timeout <br /> - Start-daemon start the synchronization daemon. Behind him can be a master or backup, to illustrate the LVS Router is the master or backup. In this function can also be used keepalived the VRRP functionality. </p><p> - Stop-daemon stop synchronization daemon <br /> -H - help Display help information <br /> -T - tcp-service service-address that the virtual server services are tcp <br /> [Vip: port] or [real-server-ip: port] <br /> -U - udp-service service-address that the virtual server service is udp <br /> [Vip: port] or [real-server-ip: port] <br /> -F - fwmark-service fwmark that is marked by the type of service iptables. <br /> -S - scheduler scheduler using the scheduling algorithm, have several options <br /> rr | wrr | lc | wlc | lblc | lblcr | dh | sh | sed | nq, <br /> The default scheduling algorithm is: </p><p> wlc. <br /> -P - persistent [timeout] persistent services. This option means that many times from the same client request will be handled the same real server. The default timeout is 300 seconds. <br /> -M - netmask netmask persistent granularity mask </p><p> -R - real-server server-address the real server [Real-Server: port] <br /> -G - gatewaying specify the operating mode for the LVS direct routing mode (default mode is LVS) <br /> -I - ipip LVS designated working mode of the tunnel mode <br /> -M - masquerading as the designated working mode of LVS NAT mode <br /> -W - weight weight weight real server <br /> - Mcast-interface interface specifies the synchronization interface to multicast <br /> -C - connection shows the current connection, such as LVS: ipvsadm-L-c <br /> - Timeout show timeout tcp tcpfin udp\'s value as: ipvsadm-L - timeout <br /> - Daemon daemon status display synchronization <br /> - Stats show statistics <br /> - Rate display rate information <br /> - Sort of virtual servers and sort out the real server <br /> - Numeric-n output IP address and port number of the form </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' p address  2, real-service-address: refers to the real server ip address  3, scheduler: Scheduling  ipvsadm usage and format are as follows:  QUOTE:  ipvsadm-A | E-t | u | f virutal-service-address: port [-s scheduler] [-p  [Timeout]] [-M netmask]  ipvsadm-D-t | u | f virtual-service-address ...'),(6,'Cluster Technology','Cluster_Technology','/a/lb/2010/0610/200.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' as 4 IP: 10.3.15.85 PORT:...','_as_4_IP_1031585_PORT','2010-06-10','2010-11-16 09:28:09','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td> as 4 IP: 10.3.15.85 PORT: 9080 Managed Server Pc1 <br /> Common PC Linux as 4 IP: 10.3.15.84 PORT: 9080 Managed Server Pc2 <br /> Common PC Linux as 4 IP: 10.3.15.85 PORT: 80 Balancer Server Pc1 <br /><br /> 1 operating system <br /> RedHat Linux as4 <br /> 2 Required Software <br /> Apache 2.0.54 Download <br /> http://apache.freelamp.com/httpd/httpd-2.0.54.tar.gz <br /> Tomcat5.5.9 Download <br /> http://apache.justdn.org/jakarta/ <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/web/tomcat/\">Tomcat</a></u> -5/v5.5.9/bin/jakarta- <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/web/tomcat/\">Tomcat</a></u> -5.5.9.tar.gz <br /> Mod_jk 1.2.14 Download <br /> http://apache.justdn.org/jakarta/tomcat-connectors/jk/source/jk-1.2.14/jakarta-tomcat-connectors-1.2.14-src.tar.gz <br /> Jdk 1_5_0_04 Download <br /> http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.5.0/download.jsp <br /> Note: Download the package file will be required in the / usr / local directory, you can also use jdk1.4 <br /> 3 Installation Steps <br /> Install JDK 3.1 <br /> # Cd / usr / local / <br /> # Chmod 777 jdk-1_5_0_04-linux-i586-rpm.bin <br /> # ./jdk-1.5.0_04-linux-i586-rpm.bin <br /> # Cd / usr / java / <br /> # Ln-s / usr/java/jdk-1_5_0_04 / usr / local / java <br /> # Vi / etc / profile <br /> # Add the following <br /> JAVA_HOME = / usr / local / java / <br /> CLASSPATH = / usr / local / java / lib / dt.jar: / usr / local / java / lib / tools.jar <br /> PATH = / usr / local / java / bin: $ PATH <br /> export PATH JAVA_HOME CLASSPATH <br /><br /> Installing Apache 3.2 <br /> # Cd / usr / local / <br /> # Tar xvfz httpd-2.0.54.tar.gz <br /> # Cd httpd-2.0.54 <br /> #. / Configure-prefix = / usr / local / apache-enable-module = so <br /> # Make <br /> # Make install <br /> # Cd / usr / local / apache / conf <br /> # Vi. / Httpd.conf <br /> Listen 80 will be modified to Listen &lt;Your IP&gt;: 80 <br /> Will be revised ServerName ServerName &lt;HOST-NAME&gt;: 80 <br /> Add in the DirectoryIndex index.jsp <br /> # Cd / usr / local / apache / bin / <br /> #. / Apachectl configtest <br /> If the display indicates a successful installation Syntax ok <br /> #. / Apachectl start <br /> Start the apache service, access to port 80 of the machine to see whether the normal port <br /> #. / Apachectl stop <br /> Close Services Note: prefix defined in the installation path of apache <br /><br /> Install Tomcat 3.3 <br /> # Cd / usr / local / <br /> # Tar xvfz jakarta-tomcat-5.5.9.tar.gz <br /> # Ln-s / usr/local/jakarta-tomcat-5.5.9 / usr / local / tomcat <br /> # Vi / usr / local / tomcat / bin / catalina.sh <br /> JAVA_HOME = / usr / local / java <br /> Start the service, access to the local 8080 port, see the port is normal <br /> # / Usr / local / tomcat / bin / startup.sh / startup.bat <br /> Close Service <br /> # / Usr / local / tomcat / bin / shutdown.sh / shutdown.bat <br /> 3.4 Installation JK <br /> # Cd / usr / local / <br /> # Tar xzvf jakarta-tomcat-connectors-1.2.14-src.tar.gz <br /> # Cd jakarta-tomcat-connectors-1.2.14-src/jk/native <br /> # Chmod 755 buildconf.sh <br /> #. / Buildconf.sh <br /> #. / Configure-with-apxs = / usr / local / apache / bin / apxs <br /> # Make <br /> # Make install <br /> # Cd / usr / local / jakarta-tomcat-connectors-jk1.2.14-src/jk/native/apache-2.0 / <br /> # Cp mod_jk.so / usr / local / apache / modules / <br /><br /> 4 System Integration <br /> 4.1 at the end of the file add the following statements best <br /> # Vi / usr / local / apache / conf / httpd.conf <br /><br /> # Load mod_jk <br /> LoadModule jk_module modules / mod_jk.so <br /> # Configure mod_jk <br /> JkWorkersFile conf / workers.properties <br /> JkLogFile logs / mod_jk.log <br /> JkLogLevel info <br /> JkMount / *. jsp loadbalancer <br /> JkMount / servlet / * loadbalancer <br /> JkMount / application / * loadbalancer <br /><br /> Add workers.properties 4.2 <br /> # Vi / usr / local / apache / conf / workers.properties <br /> As follows: <br /><br /> worker.list = loadbalancer <br /> # Define a \'local_worker\' worker using ajp13 <br /> worker.worker1.port = 8009 <br /> worker.worker1.host = 10.3.15.84 <br /> worker.worker1.type = ajp13 <br /> worker.worker1.lbfactor = 1 <br /> worker.worker1.local_worker = 0 <br /> worker.worker1.cachesize = 1000 <br /> worker.worker1.cache_timeout = 600 <br /> worker.worker1.socket_keepalive = 1 <br /> worker.worker1.socket_timeout = 0 <br /> worker.worker1.reclycle_timeout = 300 <br /> worker.worker1.retries = 3 <br /><br /> # Define another \'local_worker\' worker using ajp13 <br /> worker.worker2.port = 8009 <br /> worker.worker2.host = 10.3.15.85 <br /> worker.worker2.type = ajp13 <br /> worker.worker2.lbfactor = 1 <br /> worker.worker2.local_worker = 1 <br /> worker.worker2.cachesize = 1000 <br /> worker.worker2.cache_timeout = 600 <br /> worker.worker2.socket_keepalive = 1 <br /> worker.worker2.socket_timeout = 0 <br /> worker.worker1.reclycle_timeout = 300 <br /> worker.worker1.retries = 3 <br /><br /> # Define the LB worker <br /> worker.loadbalancer.type = lb <br /> worker.loadbalancer.balanced_workers = worker1, worker2 <br /> worker.loadbalancer.local_worker_only = 1 <br /> worker.loadbalancer.sticky_session = true <br /> worker.loadbalancer.sticky_session_force = true <br /><br /> Note: The above defines two worker, one for worker1, the other is worker2, defines a load balancing server loadbalancer, which focus on standard configuration items in blue, the associated detailed description of the document can see the official website: http:/ / tomcat.apache.org / connectors-doc / <br /><br /> worker.list = loadbalancer <br /> Set the work load balancers, the Tomcat node can not join this list. <br /> worker.worker1.lbfactor <br /> Load balancing weight ratio greater than if the weight is assigned to this node, the request more than two nodes, such as the weight ratio of 1:1, compared with the average distribution. <br /> worker.loadbalancer.balance_workers = worker1, worker2 <br /> Specify the load balancer is responsible for the Tomcat Application node. <br /> worker.loadbalancer.sticky_session = true <br /> The cluster is to be specified hereCopy to the session, if set to true, it indicates that the session stickiness, without session replication, when a user requests units where the first distribution of Tomcat, the subsequent request would have been distributed to this Tomcat server processing; If set to false, it indicates that demand for session replication. <br /> worker.loadbalancer.sticky_session_force = true <br /> If the above sticky_session set to true, it is suggested here is also set to true, the argument that if a machine in the cluster Tomcat server does not respond after repeated requests, whether the current request, forwarded to another Tomcat server processing; this parameters sticky_session = true, the impact is relatively large, will lead to other Tomcat server forwards the request could not find the original session, so if there is a request at this time to read some of the information session, it would cause the application of null exception. <br /><br /> 4.3 Modify server.xml <br /> # Vi / usr / local / tomcat / conf / server.xml <br /> Around line 120 add the following statement <br /> &lt;Engine Name=&quot;Standalone&quot; defaultHost=&quot;localhost&quot; jvmRoute=&quot;tomcat1&quot;&gt; &lt;/ Engine&gt; <br /> If the second worker1, will be modified as worker2 jvmRoute <br /> And released the following cluster configuration, which is removed comments. <br /> &lt;Cluster className = &quot;org.apache.catalina.cluster.tcp.SimpleTcpCluster&quot; <br /> managerClassName = &quot;org.apache.catalina.cluster.session.DeltaManager&quot; <br /> expireSessionsOnShutdown = &quot;false&quot; <br /> useDirtyFlag = &quot;true&quot;&gt; <br /><br /> &lt;Membership <br /> className = &quot;org.apache.catalina.cluster.mcast.McastService&quot; <br /> mcastAddr = &quot;228.0.0.4&quot; <br /> mcastPort = &quot;45564&quot; <br /> mcastFrequency = &quot;500&quot; <br /> mcastDropTime = &quot;3000&quot; /&gt; <br /><br /> &lt;Receiver <br /> className = &quot;org.apache.catalina.cluster.tcp.ReplicationListener&quot; <br /> tcpListenAddress = &quot;10.3.15.85&quot; <br /> tcpListenPort = &quot;4001&quot; <br /> tcpSelectorTimeout = &quot;100&quot; <br /> tcpThreadCount = &quot;6&quot; /&gt; <br /><br /> &lt;Sender <br /> className = &quot;org.apache.catalina.cluster.tcp.ReplicationTransmitter&quot; <br /> replicationMode = &quot;pooled&quot; /&gt; <br /> &lt;Valve className = &quot;org.apache.catalina.cluster.tcp.ReplicationValve&quot; <br /> filter = &quot;.* \\. gif; .* \\. js; .* \\. jpg; .* \\. htm; .* \\. html; .* \\. txt;&quot; /&gt; <br /> &lt;Deployer className = &quot;org.apache.catalina.cluster.deploy.FarmWarDeployer&quot; <br /> tempDir = &quot;/ tmp / war-temp /&quot; <br /> deployDir = &quot;/ tmp / war-deploy /&quot; <br /> watchDir = &quot;/ tmp / war-listen /&quot; <br /> watchEnabled = &quot;false&quot; /&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Cluster&gt; <br /><br /> At this point, the entire system has been completed and start the apache tomcat service <br /> # / Usr / local / apache / bin / apachectl start <br /> # / Usr / local / tomcat / bin / catalina.sh start <br /> Add the following to / etc / rc.d / rc.local end of the file to open after system startup apache, tomcat service <br /> / Usr / local / tomcat / bin / catalina.sh start <br /> / Usr / local / apache / bin / apachectl start <br /><br /> 5 Test the cluster <br /><br /> After all of the above steps, a two node cluster has been configured tomcat, but sometimes may not be copied conversation among peers, because all nodes must server.xml in tcpListenAddress = &quot;auto&quot; to tcpListenAddress = &quot; 10.3.15.85 &quot;, that is, to the real ip address. <br /> If activated, the following message appears: skipping state transfer. No members active in cluster group. Also need to modify the above information. Otherwise, session is not replicated between multiple tomcat\'s session. <br /><br /> 5.1 Write a simple web application, including the following: <br /> Write a the following two jsp pages. <br /> test.jsp as follows: <br /> &lt;% @ Page contentType = &quot;text / html; charset = GBK&quot;%&gt; <br /> &lt;% @ Page import = &quot;com.WorkerBean&quot;%&gt; <br /> &lt;% @ Page import = &quot;java.net .*&quot;%&gt; <br /> &lt;html&gt; <br /> &lt;head&gt; <br /> &lt;title&gt; <br /> test <br /> &lt;/ Title&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Head&gt; <br /><br /> &lt;body bgcolor=&quot;#ffffff&quot;&gt; <br /> &lt;% = Request.getSession (). GetId ()%&gt; <br /><br /> &lt;% <br /> int i = 0; <br /> WorkerBean test = new WorkerBean (); <br /> / / HttpSession tsession = request.getSession (); <br /> test.setWorker_no (request.getSession (). getId () + i); <br /> session.setAttribute (&quot;worker_no&quot;, test.getWorker_no ()); <br /><br /> System.out.println (&quot;OK&quot;); <br /> System.out.println (&quot;session.getAttribute ()==&quot;+ session.getAttribute (&quot; worker_no &quot;)); <br /> out.println (&quot;session.getAttribute ()==&quot;+ session.getAttribute (&quot; worker_no &quot;)); out.println (&quot; OK &quot;); <br /><br /> %&gt; <br /> &lt;a href=&quot;testResult.jsp&quot;&gt; testResult.jsp &lt;/ a&gt; <br /> &lt;h1&gt; Tomcat &lt;/ h1&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Body&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Html&gt; <br /><br /> testResult.jsp as follows <br /> &lt;% @ Page contentType = &quot;text / html; charset = GBK&quot;%&gt; <br /> &lt;% @ Page import = &quot;com.WorkerBean&quot;%&gt; <br /> &lt;% @ Page import = &quot;java.net .*&quot;%&gt; <br /> &lt;html&gt; <br /> &lt;head&gt; <br /> &lt;title&gt; <br /> test <br /> &lt;/ Title&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Head&gt; <br /><br /> &lt;body bgcolor=&quot;#ffffff&quot;&gt; <br /><br /> &lt;% <br /><br /> System.out.println (&quot;OK&quot;); <br /> System.out.println (&quot;session.getAttribute ()==&quot;+ session.getAttribute (&quot; worker_no &quot;)); <br /> out.println (&quot;OK&quot;); out.println (&quot;session.getAttribute ()==&quot;+ session.getAttribute (&quot; worker_no &quot;)); <br /> %&gt; <br /> &lt;h1&gt; Tomcat &lt;/ h1&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Body&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Html&gt; <br /><br /><br /> 5.2 The preparation of the jsp call javaBean class. <br /><br /> WorkerBean.java <br /> public class WorkerBean implements java.io.Serializable { <br /> String worker_no; <br /><br /> / ** <br /> Ã¯ÂÂ¬ @ return Returns worker_no. <br /> * / <br /> public String getWorker_no () { <br /> return worker_no; <br /> } <br /><br /> / ** <br /> Ã¯ÂÂ¬ @ param worker_no to set worker_no. <br /> * / <br /> public void setWorker_no (String worker_no) { <br /> this.worker_no = worker_no; <br /> } <br /><br /> } <br /><br /> Note: This class must implement serialization, object to the existence of this class session, session is to copy in the cluster, or session object can not be replicated in the cluster. <br /> 5.3 configuring web.xml file NOTE: Be sure to add &lt;distributable/&gt;, and other common application is the same. <br /> &lt;? Xml version = &quot;1.0&quot; encoding = &quot;UTF-8&quot;?&gt; <br /> &lt;! DOCTYPE web-app PUBLIC &quot;- / / Sun Microsystems, Inc. / / DTD Web Application 2.3 / / EN&quot; &quot;http://java.sun.com/dtd/web-app_2_3.dtd&quot;&gt; <br /> &lt;web-app&gt; <br /> &lt;display-name&gt; web &lt;/ display-name&gt; <br /> &lt;distributable/&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Web-app&gt; <br /> 5.4 ensure that the server.xml as shown in Appendix 1 and Appendix 2: slightly <br /> 5.5 publish web applications, to test all of the above files to tomcat\'s webapps / ROOT directory, overwrite the original file on it. <br /> Test start apache web 5.6 applications and tomcat1 and tomcat2. <br /> In the browser address bar will see the following page http://10.3.15.85/ <br /><br /> In the browser address bar will see the following page http://10.3.15.85/test.jsp <br /><br /> Click above to page 2.jsp connection, enter the following page <br /><br /><br /><br /> The output of the console can be found with the watch, 2 turns of the response to the request tomcat. <br /> Then, any one of them off tomcat, and then click 2.jsp, or can be responsive. Note the cluster automatically take over the application of machine error and found the value of which is the same session, that session in the cluster between the different tomcat session replication. <br /><br /> Summary: Through the above tests and other tools of the test and found that if two machines for tomcat cluster, tomcat more than one individual may support more concurrent, and can do a wrong, the other automatically takes over. 2 sets of separate but no support was complicated by multiple tomcat. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' as 4 IP: 10.3.15.85 PORT: 9080 Managed Server Pc1  Common PC Linux as 4 IP: 10.3.15.84 PORT: 9080 Managed Server Pc2  Common PC Linux as 4 IP: 10.3.15.85 PORT: 80 Balancer Server Pc1  1 operating system  RedHat Linux as4  2 Required Software  Apache 2.0.54 Download ...'),(7,'Cluster Technology','Cluster_Technology','/a/lb/2010/0520/106.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' -Size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning:...','_Size_9pt_msofontkerning','2010-05-20','2010-11-16 09:29:05','<html><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td> -Size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial &quot;&gt; We are here to introduce the four components: <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: \"Verdana\",\"sans-serif\"; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\"><br /> Ã‚Â· Ipchains <br /> Ã‚Â· Ipvsadm, ( <span style