ices, you can see the official documentation rhcs, <br /> Also tell you a message, an integrated IPMI devices for the master machine, you can select the fence device into the IPMI LAN, directly RHAS4. 4 comes with the IPMI service will be able to drive up, and can work, 2 Ethernet ports IPMI machine directly connected, but if there is a machine completely unplug the power, then switching will have problems, it is estimated RHCS a problem, because only in the fence command preparation unit must wait until after a successful return to take over the service, but the host power line of regard, and there can be no recovery, and results available to the machine will always show fence failed, and not to take over the service, which is not a BUG RHCS it? </p><p> hqonline </p><p> As far as I understand, fence device as follows from the role that, when an accident causes the service to stop or when the host machine, LINUX in order to ensure data integrity, reboot the host before the service, issued by the heavy equipment machine signals from the machine , the host machine restarts, the process, prepare the opportunity to take over services. fence device is the signal sent from the heavy equipment. </p><p> aquaofchina </p><p> I was assigned an implementation using HP-iLO, feeling that in order to ensure exclusive shared disk, and only wait to receive the fault signal to restart the machine has started, prepare machine began to take over the service. ILO is the first failure the machine sends a reboot signal port, and then began to stage the machine from the failure to take the machine iLO state until taken to the state is DOWN. </p><p><br /> ibm pc server + rhas4.4 + rhcs4.4 configuration method of fence <br /> hqonline </p><p> This post is to answer simonocn problems, while for everyone to share what <br /> ibm pc server + rhas4.4 + rhcs4.4 configuration fence the following ways: <br /> Hardware: <br /> 1, 2, server, configured in the BIOS, BMC\'s IP address, such as 192.168.